"title": "5947: shame",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5947: shame",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An uncomfortable feeling of guilt and humiliation, usually arising from sin or failure.</p>\n<h2>Shame is to be avoided</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:2\">PSA 25:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:20\">PSA 25:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:1\">PSA 31:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:17\">PSA 31:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:15\">PSA 44:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:31\">PSA 119:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:80\">PSA 119:80</a></p>\n<h2>Causes of shame</h2>\n<h3>Military defeat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:26\">2KI 19:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Natural afflictions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:25\">LUK 1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:23\">GEN 30:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:1\">ISA 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:4\">ISA 54:4</a> <em>not only childlessness but widowhood</em></p>\n<h3>Humiliation by an enemy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:19\">PSA 69:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:6-Ps69:7\">PSA 69:6–69:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:2\">1SA 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:4-2Sam10:5\">2SA 10:4–10:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:17\">ISA 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:4\">MRK 12:4</a></p>\n<h3>Nakedness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:18\">REV 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:25\">GEN 2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:10\">GEN 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:22-Gen9:23\">GEN 9:22–9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:3\">ISA 47:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:37\">EZK 16:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:15\">REV 16:15</a></p>\n<h3>The sin of relations or associates</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:34\">PRO 14:34</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Heathen gods as a source of shame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:10\">2SA 2:10</a></strong> <em>“Bosheth” means “shame”. According to <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr8:33\">1Ch 8:33</a> he was originally Ish-Baal, but the name “Baal”, subsequently associated with a heathen god, was changed by later writers to “Bosheth”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:24\">JER 3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:13\">JER 11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:10\">HOS 9:10</a></p>\n<h2>Shame as a divine judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:40\">JER 23:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:9\">PSA 44:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:24\">JER 46:24</a></p>\n<h3>Shame brought upon God's enemies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:10\">PSA 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:17\">PSA 31:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:26\">PSA 35:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps70:2\">PSA 70:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:13\">PSA 71:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:29\">PSA 109:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps129:5\">PSA 129:5</a></p>\n<h2>Shame as guilt for sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:6\">EZR 9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:32\">PRO 6:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:5-Dan9:7\">DAN 9:5–9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:20-Rom6:21\">ROM 6:20–6:21</a></p>\n<h3>Shame may lead to repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:5\">1CO 6:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:9-2Cor7:11\">2CO 7:9–7:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:14\">2TH 3:14</a></p>\n<h3>Some people are without shame</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:3\">JER 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:15\">JER 6:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:5\">ZEP 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ bore shame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:23\">DEU 21:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:39-Matt27:44\">MAT 27:39–27:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:6\">HEB 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>The temptation of being ashamed of Jesus Christ and the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:26\">LUK 9:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:16\">ROM 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Those who trust in God will not be put to shame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:3\">PSA 25:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:5-Ps119:6\">PSA 119:5–119:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:16\">ISA 28:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:33\">ROM 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:11\">ROM 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:6\">1PE 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:16\">1PE 4:16</a></p>",
